    <item>
      <title>Line Break ShortCode</title>
      <link>//localhost:1313/herramientas/hugo/t14-linebreakshortcode/</link>
      <pubDate>Wed, 01 Mar 2023 11:22:10 -0800</pubDate>
      <guid>//localhost:1313/herramientas/hugo/t14-linebreakshortcode/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;We can use Shortcodes to break lines.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Make line_break.html file inside layouts/shortcodes and add &lt;!-- raw HTML omitted --&gt; tag to it. So line_break.html file will look like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-php&#34; data-lang=&#34;php&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;&amp;lt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;color:#a6e22e&#34;&gt;br&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style=&#34;color:#f92672&#34;&gt;/&amp;gt;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Now you can use this Shortcode to your markdown file by adding &lt;code&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/code&gt;. So in your case, it will look like this:
&lt;img src=&#34;//localhost:1313/hugo/line_break.png&#34; alt=&#34;Widgets&#34;&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A beautiful &lt;br /&gt; other text or image&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;</description>
    </item>
